AN ACT relating to peace officers; creating the Blue Ribbon Task
Force on Peace Officer Wellness; setting forth the
membership and duties of the Task Force; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 This bill creates the Blue Ribbon Task Force on Peace Officer Wellness to
2 review the existing policies of this State concerning personal wellness initiatives
3 that account for mental and physical health of peace officers and other law
4 enforcement personnel. This bill also: (1) prescribes the membership and duties of
5 the Task Force; and (2) requires the Task Force to submit a written report
6 describing its work and recommendations for transmittal to the Senate and
7 Assembly Standing Committees on Government Affairs for the 84th Session of the
8 Legislature.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. The Blue Ribbon Task Force on Peace Officer
2 Wellness is hereby created. The Task Force consists of the
3 following eight members:
4 (a) Two members appointed by the Majority Leader of the
5 Senate;
