1 (b) One member appointed by the Minority Leader of the
2 Senate;
3 (c) Two members appointed by the Governor;
4 (d) Two members appointed by the Speaker of the Assembly;
5 and
6 (e) One member appointed by the Minority Leader of the
7 Assembly.
8 2. To the extent practicable, membership of the Task Force
9 must include, without limitation:
10 (a) A representative from a local government;
11 (b) A representative of an employer organization, as defined in
12 NRS 288.400 that represents peace officers;
13 (c) A resource officer with a behavioral health background; and
14 (d) A representative from a state law enforcement agency,
15 including, without limitation, the Department of Public Safety or the
16 Department of Corrections.
17 3. The Task Force shall:
18 (a) Review the existing policies of this State concerning
19 personal wellness initiatives that account for the mental and physical
20 health of peace officers and other law enforcement personnel; and
21 (b) Recommend personal wellness initiatives for state and local
22 law enforcement agencies.
23 4. The members of the Task Force serve without
24 compensation.
25 5. Each member of the Task Force who is an officer or
26 employee of the State or a local government must be relieved from
27 his or her duties without loss of regular compensation so that the
28 member may prepare for and attend meetings of the Task Force and
29 perform any work necessary to carry out the duties of the Task
30 Force in the most timely manner practicable. A state agency or local
31 government shall not require an officer or employee who is a
32 member of the Task Force to make up the time the member is absent
33 from work to carry out his or her duties as a member, and shall not
34 require the member to take annual vacation or compensatory time
35 for the absence.
36 6. The Task Force shall, at its first meeting, elect a Chair and
37 Vice Chair from among its members.
38 7. The Task Force shall meet upon the call of the Chair or a
39 majority of the members of the Task Force.
40 8. A majority of the members of the Task Force constitutes a
41 quorum for the transaction of business, and a majority of those
42 members present at the meeting is sufficient for any official action
43 taken by the Task Force.
