1 9. The Task Force may apply for and accept any gift, donation,
2 bequest, grant or other source of money to carry out the duties of the
3 Task Force.
4 10. The Task Force shall prepare and submit a written report to
5 the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau for transmittal to the
6 Senate and Assembly Standing Committees on Government Affairs
7 for the 84th Session of the Legislature. The report must include,
8 without limitation, a summary of the work and recommendations of
9 the Task Force.
10 Sec. 2. The members of the Task Force must be appointed
11 pursuant to section 1 of this act not later than October 1, 2025.
12 Sec. 3. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025, and expires
13 by limitation on June 30, 2027.
